   Your updated ERP outline for the Mahindra tractors dealership is well-structured and comprehensive, building on standard dealership management systems (DMS/ERP) used in automotive and equipment sectors. It covers essential operations like sales, service, inventory, and finance while incorporating key suggestions like CRM enhancements and reporting.
Core Modules

Organize into these primary modules with refined sub-modules for clarity and scalability:

Customer Management
* Enquiry Management (Service Enquiry, Tractor Enquiry)
* Quotation Management
* Lead Tracking and CRM (customer profiles, follow-ups, marketing campaigns) 
Sales & Deliveries
* Tractor Sales (pricing, financing, RTO/insurance tracking)
* Delivery Scheduling and Logistics
* Vehicle Handover and Documentation 
Service Management
* Service Scheduling and Appointments
* Job Cards and Technician Assignment
* Warranty Tracking and Claims
* Service History and Maintenance Records 
Spares & Inventory
* Spares Sales (in/out tracking, billing)
* Stock Inventory (Tractors, Spares, Accessories)
* Purchase Orders and Supplier Management
* Stock Replenishment and Forecasting 
Payments & Finance
* Payments (customer receipts, vendor payments)
* Invoicing and GST Compliance
* Day Book and Ledger Management
* Financial Reporting (P&L, balance sheets) 
Complaints & Support
* Complaint Logging and Resolution
* Feedback and Escalation Tracking
* Customer Satisfaction Surveys 
Employee Management
* Attendance Tracking
* Salary and Payroll Processing
* Work Distribution and Task Assignment
* Performance Reviews 
Reports & Analytics
* Dashboards (sales trends, inventory turnover, service KPIs)
* Custom Reports (daily/weekly/monthly summaries)
* Business Intelligence (forecasting, profitability analysis) 
Key Additions
These enhance completeness based on equipment dealership best practices:
* Supplier Portal: Automated purchase orders and vendor performance tracking.
* OEM Integration: Links to Mahindra's portal for parts pricing, warranties, and updates.
* Mobile App: For field staff to handle deliveries, service calls, and stock checks.
* Document Management: Digital storage for contracts, invoices, and compliance docs.
* Security & Access: Role-based permissions (e.g., sales vs. inventory users) and audit logs. 
Implementation Tips
Prioritize modules in phases: Start with Customer Management, Inventory, and Payments as MVP, then add Service and Reports. Use cloud-based tech for multi-location support if expanding showrooms. This structure ensures full operational coverage while remaining flexible for growth [ from prior context].
